Detailed Description

Represents the meta data of an image, which contains basic informations like the width and height of an image.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum Image::MetaData::ColorSpace
 

Describes the internally used color space from the image. When drawing the image the used color space will automatically get converted to the color space used by the display.

Enumerator:
Rgb565ColorSpace  5 bits are used for the red value, 6 bits for the green value and 5 for the blue value.
Rgb888ColorSpace  8 bits are used for the red, green and blue value.
Rgba8888ColorSpace  8 bits are used for the red, green, blue and alpha value.
Yuv420ColorSpace 
Yuv422ColorSpace
